step_data.thought:
I'm now on the Login as Customer Log page, which is exactly what I was asked to view. The page shows a table that would display the login history of admin users logging in as customers. However, I can see that there are currently '0 records found' and the message 'We couldn't find any records.' This means there is no login history to display at the moment - no admins have used the 'Login as Customer' functionality yet.

I've already cleared any filters that might have been restricting the view (in my previous action), so this is indeed the complete login history, which happens to be empty. The table headers show what information would be displayed if there were records:
- Customer ID
- Customer Email
- Admin ID
- Admin Name
- Logged In

Since I've successfully navigated to the Login as Customer Log and can see the (empty) login history, I've completed the requested task. I should inform the user about what I found.
